✅ PRACTICAL 2: HBASE OPERATIONS
Technology: HBase Shell
🎯 Objective

Perform basic CRUD operations (Create, Read, Update, Delete) in HBase.

⚙️ Steps to Perform
Start HBase
start-hbase.cmd
Open HBase Shell
hbase shell

🧾 Execution Commands
1. Create Table
create 'kccs', 'students'

  2. List Tables
list

3. Describe Table
describe 'kccs'

  4. Insert Data (PUT)
put 'kccs', '1', 'students:name', 'Dhruv'
put 'kccs', '1', 'students:roll', '59'
put 'kccs', '1', 'students:city', 'Mumbai'

  5. Retrieve Data (GET)
get 'kccs', '1'

  6. Count Rows
count 'kccs'

  
  7. Add Column Family (ALTER)
alter 'kccs', NAME => 'teachers'

  
  8. Insert into New Column Family
put 'kccs', '1', 'teachers:name', 'Mr. Naveen'

  
  9. Delete Data
delete 'kccs', '1', 'students:roll'

10. Disable & Enable Table
disable 'kccs'
enable 'kccs'

  
11. Truncate Table
truncate 'kccs'
✅ Expected Output Example
ROW COLUMN+CELL
1 column=students:name, value=Dhruv
1 column=students:city, value=Mumbai
